  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] It was [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] a frightening experience for us, the 5,000 people who were left behind.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we did not all believe that they went into the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was always this myth that they went to another camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in fact, the day before-- the night before they were killed, they each had to fill out a post card-- which was the normal thing to do-- that was post-dated a whole month.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In other words, April something, to-- to send to some relative or friend in-- back home, saying we are well.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Do not worry.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Their signature.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] As time went by, we were more and more frightened because we believed that we will [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] have the same fate, that six months after our arrival, that we will all be gassed as well.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And by then, the gas chambers were in full production with transports arriving from Hungary and Poland and all over Europe nightly.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the sky was glowing red from the crematoria, that often they had to also burn the bodies on open piles.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So the smell and the-- the smoke was pretty obvious.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Yet somehow, as a child, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we built-- as children, we built in some kind of a resistance, of not accepting it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And this myth that it's not happening, even though it was less than half a kilometer away.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Sticks with me, that-- that [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I was-- I was trying all this time not to take things in, to live day to day and not think ahead, what could happen, or could not happen.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the-- the whole experience was to be as inconspicuous as possible.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
